    "attributes": {
        "action": "Public Inquiry into Covid-19 arrangements for Approved Driving Instructors/PDIs ",
        "additional_details": "ADIs have to temporarily resign or face removal from the ADI register if they fail to take their four-yearly test, and no exceptions have been made during the current outbreak. \r\n \r\nA public inquiry should: \r\n  \r\nHave unlimited power to obtain all records from DVSA \r\nEstablish the No. of Approved Driving Instructors (ADIs) & Potential Driving Instructors (PDIs) forced to resign or are removed from ADI Register by the DVSA \r\nEstablish whether any ADIs died after being required to work or take ADI/PDI tests during COVID-19 \r\nEstablish the role of the DVSA Chief Executive & Secretary of State for Transport in decision about arrangements for ADIs ",
        "background": "There should be a Public inquiry into arrangements for Approved Driving Instructors during the Covid-19 outbreak, including why the option to defer tests has not been made available, despite 3 lockdowns and local restrictions. ",
